track_notes: This is the long way, I took a shorter way on the descent. You will need a high clearance vehicle if you plan to drive some of this. The off trail part you will want to do in the winter, there is too much low vegetation to deal with during the growing season. The summit is typical for Georgia.
Round trip. You may want to try my descent for both ways, depends on how you approach this. There is quite a bit of small trees and other low vegetation to deal with.

We parked at N34.8838, W083.5102. We started out following Ryans track. When we came to a 4-wheeler trail on the right at N34.8858, W083.5011, we took it. If you have 4-wheel drive, there is a good parking spot just before the 4-wheeler track at N34.8861, W083.5013. We followed the 4-wheeler track to a saddle at N34.8826, W083.4965. There, we took a faint trail into the woods to the left. The trail became very good after just a few dozen feet. We followed that good trail to a saddle at N34.8840, W083.4926. There we took a very faint trail to the left, following the ridgeline. We alternately lost/found/lost/found the trail, but you should just maintain the ridgeline straight to the summit. This route keeps you on-trail until that final bushwhack/faint trail.
